[4714.976411, "o", "ction,  which  is\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[17;1H\u001b[K              imposed  upon  the  set  of all processes when some BSD-style\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[18;1H\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1m-e     \u001b[22mSelect all processes.  Identical to \u001b[1m-A\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mg      \u001b[22mReally  all, even session leaders.  This flag is obsolete and\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H\u001b[K              may be discontinued in a  future  release.   It  is  normally\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K              implied  by  the \u001b[1ma \u001b[22mflag, and is only useful when operating in\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[K              the sunos4 personality.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1m-N     \u001b[22mSelect all processes except those that fulfill the  specified\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K              conditions (negates the selection).  Identical to \u001b[1m--deselect\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mT      \u001b[22mSelect   all   processes   associated   with  this  terminal.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K              Identical to the \u001b[1mt \u001b[22moption without any argument.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mr      \u001b[22mRestrict the selection to o"]
[4714.977598, "o", "nly running processes.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mx      \u001b[22mLift the BSD-style \"must have a tty\"  restriction,  which  is\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[17;1H\u001b[K              imposed  upon  the  set  of all processes when some BSD-style\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[18;1H"]
[4714.978419, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       \u001b[1m\u001b[7m-j\u001b[27m\u001b[1m     \u001b[22mJobs format.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1ml      \u001b[22mDisplay BSD long format.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-l     \u001b[22mLong format.  The \u001b[1m-y \u001b[22moption is often useful with this.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-M     \u001b[22mAdd a column of security data.  Identical to \u001b[1mZ \u001b[22m(for SELinux).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mO \u001b[4m\u001b[22mformat\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              is preloaded \u001b[1mo \u001b[22m(overloaded).  The BSD \u001b[1mO \u001b[22moption can  act  like\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-O  \u001b[22m(user-defined  output  format  with  some  common  fields\u001b[m\r\n              predefined) or can be used to specify sort order.  Heuristics\u001b[m\r\n              are used to determine the behavior of this option.  To ensure\u001b[m\r\n              that  the  desired   behavior   is   obtained   (sorting   or\u001b[m\r\n              formatting), specify the option in some other way (e.g.  with\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-O  \u001b[22mor  \u001b[1m--sort\u001b[22m).   When  used  as  a formatting option, it is\u001b[m\r\n              identical to \u001b[1m-O\u001b[22m, with the BSD personality.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 285 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
