[4721.880452, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1m-j     \u001b[22mJobs format.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1ml      \u001b[22mDisplay BSD long format.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1m-l     \u001b[22mLong format.  The \u001b[1m-y \u001b[22moption is often useful with this.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1m-M     \u001b[22mAdd a column of security data.  Identical to \u001b[1mZ \u001b[22m(for SELinux).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mO \u001b[4m\u001b[22mformat\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K              is preloaded \u001b[1mo \u001b[22m(overloaded).  The BSD \u001b[1mO \u001b[22moption can  act  like\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K              \u001b[1m-O  \u001b[22m(user-defined  output  format  with  some  common  fields\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K              predefined) or can be used to specify sort order.  Heuristics\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K              are used to determine the behavior of this option.  To ensure\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H\u001b[K              that  the  desired   behavior   is   obtained   (sorting   or\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\u001b[K              formatting), specify the option in some other way (e.g.  with\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H\u001b[K              \u001b[1m-O  \u001b[22mor  \u001b[1m--sort\u001b"]
[4721.881027, "o", "[22m).   When  used  as  a formatting option, it is\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[17;1H\u001b[K              identical to \u001b[1m-O\u001b[22m, with the BSD personality.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[18;1H\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1m-j     \u001b[22mJobs format.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1ml      \u001b[22mDisplay BSD long format.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1m-l     \u001b[22mLong format.  The \u001b[1m-y \u001b[22moption is often useful with this.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1m-M     \u001b[22mAdd a column of security data.  Identical to \u001b[1mZ \u001b[22m(for SELinux).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mO \u001b[4m\u001b[22mformat\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K              is preloaded \u001b[1mo \u001b[22m(overloaded).  The BSD \u001b[1mO \u001b[22moption can  act  like\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K              \u001b[1m-O  \u001b[22m(user-defined  output  format  with  some  common  fields\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K              predefined) or can be used to specify sort order.  Heuristics\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K              are used to determine the behavior of this option.  To ensure\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H\u001b[K              that  the  desired   behavior   is   obtained   (sorting   or\u001b[m\r\n"]
[4721.881933, "o", "\u001b[15;1H\u001b[K              formatting), specify the option in some other way (e.g.  with\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H\u001b[K              \u001b[1m-O  \u001b[22mor  \u001b[1m--sort\u001b[22m).   When  used  as  a formatting option, it is\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[17;1H\u001b[K              identical to \u001b[1m-O\u001b[22m, with the BSD personality.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[18;1H"]
[4721.882312, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       \u001b[1m\u001b[7m-H\u001b[27m\u001b[1m     \u001b[22mShow process hierarchy (forest).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m--headers\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              Repeat header lines, one per page of output.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mk \u001b[4m\u001b[22mspec\u001b[24m Specify     sorting     order.      Sorting     syntax     is\u001b[m\r\n              [\u001b[1m+\u001b[22m|\u001b[1m-\u001b[22m]\u001b[4mkey\u001b[24m[,[\u001b[1m+\u001b[22m|\u001b[1m-\u001b[22m]\u001b[4mkey\u001b[24m[,...]].  Choose a  multi-letter  key  from\u001b[m\r\n              the  \u001b[1mSTANDARD FORMAT SPECIFIERS \u001b[22msection.  The \"+\" is optional\u001b[m\r\n              since  default   direction   is   increasing   numerical   or\u001b[m\r\n              lexicographic order.  Identical to \u001b[1m--sort\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n                      Examples:\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mps jaxkuid,-ppid,+pid\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mps axk comm o comm,args\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mps kstart_time -ef\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m--lines \u001b[4m\u001b[22mn\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 393 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
