[4909.802803, "o", "\u001b[4mPS\u001b[24m(1)                       User Commands                       \u001b[4mPS\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       ps - report a snapshot of the current processes.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mps \u001b[22m[\u001b[4moptions\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mps \u001b[22mdisplays information about a selection of the active\u001b[m\r\n       processes.  If you want a repetitive update of the selection\u001b[m\r\n       and the displayed information, use \u001b[1mtop \u001b[22minstead.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       This version of \u001b[1mps \u001b[22maccepts several kinds of options:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4910.801934, "o", "\r\u001b[K/"]
[4911.021697, "o", "\u001b[Ks\bs"]
