[4911.657788, "o", "\u001b[Kt\bt"]
[4911.815513, "o", "\u001b[Ke\be"]
[4912.040422, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[4912.041977, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K\u001b[4mPS\u001b[24m(1)                       User Commands                       \u001b[4mPS\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H\u001b[K       ps - report a snapshot of the current processes.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mps \u001b[22m[\u001b[4moptions\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mps \u001b[22mdisplays information about a selection of the active\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K       processes.  If you want a repetitive update of the selection\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K       and the displayed information, use \u001b[1mtop \u001b[22minstead.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H\u001b[K       This version of \u001b[1mps \u001b[22maccepts several kinds of options:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K\u001b[4mPS\u001b[24m(1)                       User Commands                       \u001b[4mPS\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H\u001b[K       ps - report a snapshot of the current processes.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mps \u001b[22m[\u001b[4moptions\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K"]
[4912.04279, "o", "\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mps \u001b[22mdisplays information about a selection of the active\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K       processes.  If you want a repetitive update of the selection\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K       and the displayed information, use \u001b[1mtop \u001b[22minstead.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H\u001b[K       This version of \u001b[1mps \u001b[22maccepts several kinds of options:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H"]
[4912.043078, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       The   use   of   BSD-style  options  will  add  process  \u001b[7mstate\u001b[27m\u001b[m\r\n       (stat=STAT) to the default display and show the  command  args\u001b[m\r\n       (args=COMMAND)  instead  of  the  executable  name.   You  can\u001b[m\r\n       override this with the \u001b[1mPS_FORMAT  \u001b[22menvironment  variable.   The\u001b[m\r\n       use   of  BSD-style  options  will  also  change  the  process\u001b[m\r\n       selection to include processes on other terminals (TTYs)  that\u001b[m\r\n       are  owned  by  you;  alternately,  this  may  be described as\u001b[m\r\n       setting the selection to be the set of all processes  filtered\u001b[m\r\n       to  exclude  processes  owned  by  other  users  or  not  on a\u001b[m\r\n       terminal.  These effects are not considered when  options  are\u001b[m\r\n       described as being \"identical\" below, so \u001b[1m-M \u001b[22mwill be considered\u001b[m\r\n       identical to \u001b[1mZ \u001b[22mand so on.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Except  as  described  below,  process  selection  options are\u001b[m\r\n       additive.  The default selection is discarded,  and  then  the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 35 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4912.792446, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[4912.794635, "o", "...skipping...\r\n              Identical to \u001b[1m-o pid,\u001b[4m\u001b[22mformat\u001b[24m\u001b[1m,\u001b[7mstate\u001b[27m\u001b[22m\u001b[24m\u001b[1m,tname,time,command  \u001b[22mor\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-o pid,\u001b[4m\u001b[22mformat\u001b[24m\u001b[1m,tname,time,cmd\u001b[22m, see \u001b[1m-o \u001b[22mbelow.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mo \u001b[4m\u001b[22mformat\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              Specify  user-defined  format.   Identical  to  \u001b[1m-o  \u001b[22mand\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m--format\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-o \u001b[4m\u001b[22mformat\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              User-defined format.  \u001b[4mformat\u001b[24m is a  single  argument  in\u001b[m\r\n              the  form of a blank-separated or comma-separated list,\u001b[m\r\n              which  offers  a  way  to  specify  individual   output\u001b[m\r\n              columns.   The recognized keywords are described in the\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mSTANDARD FORMAT SPECIFIERS \u001b[22msection below.  Headers  may\u001b[m\r\n              be  renamed  (\u001b[1mps -o pid,ruser=RealUser -o comm=Command\u001b[22m)\u001b[m\r\n              as desired.  If all column headers  are  empty  (\u001b[1mps  -o\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 326 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4918.846911, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[4918.848681, "o", "...skipping...\r\n\u001b[1mPROCESS \u001b[7mSTATE\u001b[27m\u001b[1m CODES\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       Here are the different values  that  the  \u001b[1ms\u001b[22m,  \u001b[1mstat  \u001b[22mand  \u001b[1m\u001b[7mstate\u001b[27m\u001b[1m\u001b[22m\u001b[1m\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       output  specifiers  (header  \"STAT\"  or  \"S\")  will display to\u001b[m\r\n       describe the \u001b[7mstate\u001b[27m of a process:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n               D    uninterruptible sleep (usually IO)\u001b[m\r\n               I    Idle kernel thread\u001b[m\r\n               R    running or runnable (on run queue)\u001b[m\r\n               S    interruptible sleep  (waiting  for  an  event  to\u001b[m\r\n                    complete)\u001b[m\r\n               T    stopped by job control signal\u001b[m\r\n               t    stopped by debugger during the tracing\u001b[m\r\n               W    paging (not valid since the 2.6.xx kernel)\u001b[m\r\n               X    dead (should never be seen)\u001b[m\r\n               Z    defunct  (\"zombie\")  process,  terminated but not\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 564 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4919.893319, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[4919.893602, "o", "                    reaped by its parent\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 565 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4920.225006, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n       For BSD formats and when the \u001b[1mstat \u001b[22mkeyword is used,  additional\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 567 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4920.427125, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[4920.431145, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       \u001b[1ms           \u001b[22mS         minimal  \u001b[7mstate\u001b[27m\u001b[1m\u001b[22m  display (one character).\u001b[m\r\n                             See section \u001b[1mPROCESS \u001b[7mSTATE\u001b[27m\u001b[1m CODES \u001b[22mfor  the\u001b[m\r\n                             different  values.  See also \u001b[1mstat \u001b[22mif you\u001b[m\r\n                             want additional  information  displayed.\u001b[m\r\n                             (alias \u001b[1m\u001b[7mstate\u001b[27m\u001b[1m\u001b[22m).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1msched       \u001b[22mSCH       scheduling  policy  of the process.  The\u001b[m\r\n                             policies   SCHED_OTHER   (SCHED_NORMAL),\u001b[m\r\n                             SCHED_FIFO,    SCHED_RR,    SCHED_BATCH,\u001b[m\r\n                             SCHED_ISO, SCHED_IDLE and SCHED_DEADLINE\u001b[m\r\n                             are respectively displayed as 0,  1,  2,\u001b[m\r\n                             3, 4, 5 and 6.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mseat        \u001b[22mSEAT      displays  the identifier associated with\u001b[m\r\n                             all  hardware  devices  assigned  to   a\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 1076 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4920.63652, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[4920.636615, "o", "                             specific  workplace,  if systemd support\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 1077 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4921.098427, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K                             has been included.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1msess        \u001b[22mSESS      session ID or, equivalently, the process\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 1080 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4921.380779, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[4921.382092, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       \u001b[1mstat        \u001b[22mSTAT      multi-character  process   \u001b[7mstate\u001b[27m\u001b[1m\u001b[22m.    See\u001b[m\r\n                             section  \u001b[1mPROCESS  \u001b[7mSTATE\u001b[27m\u001b[1m  CODES  \u001b[22mfor  the\u001b[m\r\n                             different  values  meaning.   See   also\u001b[m\r\n                             \u001b[1ms \u001b[22mand \u001b[1m\u001b[7mstate\u001b[27m\u001b[1m\u001b[22m\u001b[1m  \u001b[22mif  you just want the first\u001b[m\r\n                             character displayed.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m\u001b[7mstate\u001b[27m\u001b[1m       \u001b[22mS         see \u001b[1ms\u001b[22m. (alias \u001b[1ms\u001b[22m).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mstime       \u001b[22mSTIME     see \u001b[1mstart_time\u001b[22m. (alias \u001b[1mstart_time\u001b[22m).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1msuid        \u001b[22mSUID      saved user ID.  (alias \u001b[1msvuid\u001b[22m).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1msupgid      \u001b[22mSUPGID    group ids of  supplementary  groups,  if\u001b[m\r\n                             any.  See \u001b[1mgetgroups\u001b[22m(2).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 1151 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4921.732837, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K       \u001b[1msupgrp      \u001b[22mSUPGRP    group  names of supplementary groups, if\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 1152 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4922.453373, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K                             any.  See \u001b[1mgetgroups\u001b[22m(2).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 1154 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4922.662322, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K       \u001b[1msuser       \u001b[22mSUSER     saved  user  name.   This  will  be  the\u001b[m\r\n                             textual  user  ID, if it can be obtained\u001b[m\r\n                             and  the  field  width  permits,  or   a\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ps(1) line 1157 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[4922.819915, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
